@felixbarny I missed a method onStream on #1172 so will create a follow PR to add that one as well.
Locally, it seems the span is now correctly passed along the AsyncHandler but there is still a place in my test setup where the span is not correctly passed on through all the Scala Futures.
I will investigate further but I am maybe thinking there was a reason why other solutions instrument the Promise directly and not the ExecutionContext.

